# Monorepo Tooling

This is a pnpm + Turborepo monorepo. Use the right tool.

## Package manager

- **pnpm only.** Never `npm`, `yarn`, `bun`, or `npx` (use `pnpm dlx`).
- Root-level dependencies: `pnpm add -w <pkg>`.
- Package-scoped dependencies: `pnpm --filter @gamevine/<pkg> add <dep>`.
- Internal packages: reference with `"workspace:*"` in `package.json`.
- Never hand-edit `pnpm-lock.yaml`. Let pnpm regenerate it.
- Required versions per `package.json#engines`: Node `>=20.19`, pnpm `>=10`.

## Turborepo

- Use `turbo run <task>` via the top-level scripts (`pnpm dev`, `pnpm build`, `pnpm lint`, `pnpm test`, `pnpm typecheck`).
- Scope a run with `--filter`: `pnpm exec turbo run build --filter=@gamevine/web`.
- When adding a new task, register it in `turbo.json` with the correct `dependsOn`, `inputs`, `outputs`, and `env`. A missing `^build` dependency is the most common cache bug in this repo.

## Workspace layout (do not invent new top-levels)

- `apps/web` — Next.js frontend
- `apps/api` — NestJS backend
- `packages/shared` — cross-app types/constants
- `packages/eslint-config` — shared ESLint config
- `packages/tsconfig` — shared TS configs

New application? Put it in `apps/`. New library consumed by multiple apps? `packages/`.

## Running commands in the right place

| Intent                     | Command                                    |
| -------------------------- | ------------------------------------------ |
| Run everything             | `pnpm dev` (root)                          |
| Run just the web app       | `pnpm dev:web` (root)                      |
| Run just the api           | `pnpm dev:api` (root)                      |
| Execute inside one package | `pnpm --filter @gamevine/<pkg> <script>`   |
| Ad-hoc exec in a package   | `pnpm --filter @gamevine/<pkg> exec <cmd>` |

## Forbidden

- Creating a second lockfile (`package-lock.json`, `yarn.lock`, `bun.lockb`).
- Installing the same dependency in both apps when it could live in `packages/shared`.
- Hoisting via root `dependencies` instead of using `workspace:*`.
- `pnpm install --force` without a stated reason.
